conditions.name: Admission Rescheduling Condition
conditions.description: Condition for rescheduling admission to CRU on Day 1.
conditions.text: Plasma Glucose (PG) level is not 90 to 250 mg/dL on Day 1.

conditions.name: Insulin Infusion Stop Condition
conditions.description: Condition to stop the insulin infusion used to induce hypoglycemia.

conditions.name: Fasting Requirement
conditions.description: Fasting requirement for sample collection in Periods 1 and 2.
conditions.text: At Periods 1 and 2, samples should be collected from patients who have fasted at least 8 hours before any study procedures.

conditions.name: Interim Safety Review Trigger
conditions.description: Condition triggering an interim safety review to decide on study continuation.
conditions.text: Safety data will be reviewed after the first 6 patients (regardless of type of diabetes) are administered LY900018 in Period 2.

conditions.name: TE ADA Positive
conditions.text: Patients with treatment-emergent antidrug antibodies (TE ADA) at follow-up/ED will undergo additional follow-up.

conditions.name: Patient Replacement Criteria
conditions.description: Condition for replacing a discontinued patient.
conditions.text: If patients discontinue from the study before completion of both periods with evaluable primary outcome for any reason, the patient may be replaced. Replacement should not occur beyond 75 patients enrolled.

transitionRules.name: Transition to Additional Follow-up
transitionRules.text: Patients with TE ADA at follow-up/ED will undergo additional follow-up.

transitionRules.name: Procedures on Premature Discontinuation
transitionRules.text: Patients discontinuing from the study prematurely for any reason must complete AE and follow-up procedures as shown in the Schedule of Activities.

transitionRules.name: Handling of Inadvertently Enrolled Patients
transitionRules.text: If a patient who did not meet enrollment criteria was inadvertently enrolled, a discussion must occur between the Lilly CP/CRP and the investigator to determine if the patient may continue in the study.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Study Completion
scheduleTimelineExits.description: Completion of all protocol-required visits, including the final follow-up visit.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Completion of Additional Follow-up
scheduleTimelineExits.description: Additional follow-up for TE ADA completes when the titer returns to baseline or until 1 year after the last dose of study treatment.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Discontinuation due to Other Study
scheduleTimelineExits.description: Patient is discontinued for enrollment in any other clinical study involving an investigational product or judged not to be scientifically or medically compatible with this study.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Discontinuation for Medical/Safety/Regulatory Reasons
scheduleTimelineExits.description: Patient is discontinued if participation needs to be stopped for medical, safety, regulatory, or other reasons consistent with applicable laws, regulations, and good clinical practice.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Discontinuation by Investigator Decision
scheduleTimelineExits.description: The investigator decides that the patient should be discontinued from the study for any reason.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Withdrawal of Consent
scheduleTimelineExits.description: The patient, or legal representative, requests to be withdrawn from the study.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Study Termination for Safety
scheduleTimelineExits.description: The entire study will be stopped if deemed necessary for patient safety following the review of data from the first 6 patients to complete Period 2 Day 1.

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Lost to Follow-up
scheduleTimelineExits.description: A patient will be considered lost to follow-up if he or she repeatedly fails to return for scheduled visits and is unable to be contacted by the study site.

scheduledDecisionInstances.name: Interim Safety Review Decision
scheduledDecisionInstances.description: Decision point to continue dosing remaining patients or stop the study based on safety review of the first 6 patients. If no clinically significant safety findings are noted, the remaining patients will be dosed.

scheduledDecisionInstances.name: Inadvertent Enrollment Decision
scheduledDecisionInstances.description: Decision point for inadvertently enrolled patients to determine if they may continue in the study, requiring documented approval from the sponsor.
